      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 2.28,
      "endTime": 11.3
    },
    {
      "id": "intro_3",
      "role": "Narrator",
      "text": "What important thing did King Alfred learn when he penetrated the Danish camp of Guthrum?",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 11.31,
      "endTime": 20.71,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "What",
            "label": "疑问词"
          }
        ],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "What",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "什么"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "intro_4",
      "role": "Narrator",
      "text": "Alfred the Great acted as his own spy, visiting Danish camps disguised as a minstrel.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 20.72,
      "endTime": 29.53,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "his",
            "label": "形容词性物主代词"
          }
        ],
        "words": []
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s1",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "In those days wandering minstrels were welcome everywhere.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 29.54,
      "endTime": 34.44
    },
    {
      "id": "s2",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "They were not fighting men, and their harp was their passport.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 34.45,
      "endTime": 39.19,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "their",
            "label": "形容词性物主代词"
          },
          {
            "text": "their",
            "label": "形容词性物主代词"
          }
        ],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "Not",
            "pos": "adv.",
            "meaning": "不，不是"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s3",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "Alfred had learned many of their ballads in his youth and could vary his programme with acrobatic tricks and simple conjuring.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 39.2,
      "endTime": 49.16,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "their",
            "label": "形容词性物主代词"
          },
          {
            "text": "his",
            "label": "形容词性物主代词"
          },
          {
            "text": "his",
            "label": "形容词性物主代词"
          }
        ],
        "words": []
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s4",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "While Alfred's little army slowly began to gather at Athelney, the king himself set out to penetrate the camp of Guthrum, the commander of the Danish invaders.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 49.17,
      "endTime": 62.25,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "At",
            "pos": "prep.",
            "meaning": "在...（小地点/时刻）"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s5",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "These had settled down for the winter at Chippenham: thither Alfred went.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 62.26,
      "endTime": 69.31,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "At",
            "pos": "prep.",
            "meaning": "在...（小地点/时刻）"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s6",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "He noticed at once that discipline was slack: the Danes had the self-confidence of conquerors, and their security precautions were casual.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 69.32,
      "endTime": 81.05,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "that",
            "label": "指示代词"
          },
          {
            "text": "their",
            "label": "形容词性物主代词"
          }
        ],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "At",
            "pos": "prep.",
            "meaning": "在...（小地点/时刻）"
          },
          {
            "word": "That",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "那个"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s7",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "They lived well, on the proceeds of raids on neighbouring regions.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 81.06,
      "endTime": 86.76,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "Well",
            "pos": "adj.",
            "meaning": "健康的，良好的"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s8",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "There they collected women as well as food and drink, and a life of ease had made them soft.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 86.77,
      "endTime": 94.88,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "Well",
            "pos": "adj.",
            "meaning": "健康的，良好的"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s9",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "Alfred stayed in the camp a week before he returned to Athelney.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 94.89,
      "endTime": 100.12
    },
    {
      "id": "s10",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "The force there assembled was trivial compared with the Danish horde.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 100.13,
      "endTime": 105.11
    },
    {
      "id": "s11",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "But Alfred had deduced that the Danes were no longer fit for prolonged battle: and that their commissariat had no organization, but depended on irregular raids.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 105.12,
      "endTime": 118.51,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "that",
            "label": "指示代词"
          },
          {
            "text": "that",
            "label": "指示代词"
          },
          {
            "text": "their",
            "label": "形容词性物主代词"
          }
        ],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "That",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "那个"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s12",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "So, faced with the Danish advance, Alfred did not risk open battle but harried the enemy.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 118.52,
      "endTime": 126.56,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "Not",
            "pos": "adv.",
            "meaning": "不，不是"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s13",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "He was constantly on the move, drawing the Danes after him.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 126.57,
      "endTime": 131.57
    },
    {
      "id": "s14",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "His patrols halted the raiding parties: hunger assailed the Danish army.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 131.58,
      "endTime": 137.96,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "His",
            "label": "形容词性物主代词"
          }
        ],
        "words": []
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s15",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "Now Alfred began a long series of skirmishes -- and within a month the Danes had surrendered.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 137.97,
      "endTime": 145.73
    },
    {
      "id": "s16",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "The episode could reasonably serve as a unique epic of royal espionage!",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 145.74,
      "endTime": 150.74
    }
  ]
